Election for a Johannesburg mayor has been postponed to 4 December 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The vote for a new Johannesburg mayor has been postponed to 4 December 2019. The council was expected to vote in a new mayor, after Herman Mashaba officially ended his term on Wednesday. READ: Tshwane, Johannesburg up for grabs The ANC has announced Geoff Makhubo as its mayoral candidate. The DA and EFF have already put forward candidates.